      </div>

      <div class="bento-card">
        <div class="bento-num">✗</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Skip Nightwatch if</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">You need <span class="accent">content written, GBP managed, or social posts published.</span></h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Nightwatch measures rankings. It doesn't move them. No content creation, no GBP, no social — everything that builds the traffic you're tracking needs to happen elsewhere.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See why theStacc fits better <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS NIGHTWATCH -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">What is Nightwatch</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">The rank tracker with <span class="accent">ZIP-code precision</span> and AI citation monitoring.</h2>
      <p>Nightwatch was founded in 2016 in Ljubljana, Slovenia, and serves over 10,000 teams globally — including companies like Google, Uber, and Tripadvisor. The platform monitors keyword rankings across Google, Bing, Yahoo, DuckDuckGo, and YouTube with ZIP-code granularity across 107,000+ locations. The 2026 version adds Citation Intelligence, which tracks brand and keyword mentions across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity — connecting AI search visibility to traditional SERP rankings.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">What separates Nightwatch from commoditized rank trackers is local precision. Most tools track at the city level. Nightwatch tracks at the ZIP code — which matters enormously for service-area businesses, multi-location retail, and local SEO agencies trying to demonstrate value in specific neighborhoods. No competitor matches this granularity.</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">The white-label reporting is polished: branded PDFs, client dashboards, automated scheduling, and Looker Studio integration on Professional+ plans. Unlimited team seats on every plan means agencies don't pay per-user fees. The trade-off is clear: Nightwatch tracks. It doesn't create content, manage GBP, build citations, or post to social. If you need any of those, they live outside the product.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROS / CONS -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The honest pros &amp; cons</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">What Nightwatch gets right — <span class="accent">and where it lets you down.</span></h2>
      <p>After hands-on testing across rank tracking, local precision, site auditing, and AI citation monitoring, here's the full picture.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Pros</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Where Nightwatch shines</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Five genuine strengths that justify the price.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>ZIP-code level local tracking</h4>
              <p>107,000+ tracking locations. No competitor comes close on local granularity. For agencies reporting to clients in specific neighborhoods, this is a genuine differentiator.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Excellent white-label reporting</h4>
              <p>Clean, professional client dashboards with branded PDFs, automated scheduling, and Looker Studio integration. The reports look good enough to justify your monthly retainer without any design work from you.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Unlimited team seats on all plans</h4>
              <p>No per-user fees. Unusual in the category and genuinely valuable for agencies with multiple account managers, editors, and client-facing staff.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>AI search citation tracking</h4>
              <p>Citation Intelligence monitors brand and keyword mentions across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity. One of the few rank trackers taking AI search visibility seriously in 2026.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Strong user satisfaction</h4>
              <p>4.9/5 on G2 across 43+ reviews — among the highest-rated rank trackers in the category. Users consistently cite local tracking accuracy and client reporting as the standout features.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Cons</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Where Nightwatch falls short</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Five real weaknesses we found in testing.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>No content creation or publishing</h4>
              <p>Nightwatch measures rankings — it doesn't move them. No AI writing, no content publishing, no GBP management. Everything that builds the organic traffic you're tracking happens outside the tool.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Limited site auditing at entry level</h4>
              <p>Starter plan restricts site audits to 25 pages — not enough for any real production website. Unlimited audits only on Agency plan at €399/mo.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Shallow backlink monitoring</h4>
              <p>Backlink tracking is present but lacks the depth needed for strategic link-building or competitive link gap analysis. Ahrefs and Semrush are far stronger here.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Higher per-keyword cost than some competitors</h4>
              <p>At approximately €170 per 1,000 keywords on Starter, Nightwatch is pricier per keyword than AccuRanker and SE Ranking. For high-volume tracking, the cost adds up.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>No mobile app</h4>
              <p>Browser-only. The interface is responsive, but there's no native iOS or Android app for on-the-go monitoring.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">107K<span class="accent">+</span></div><div class="stat-label">Tracking locations · ZIP-code precision</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">€79<span class="accent">+</span></div><div class="stat-label">Starting monthly price</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">4.3<span class="accent">/5</span></div><div class="stat-label">Our rating · 4.9 on G2</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">4<span class="accent"> AI</span></div><div class="stat-label">LLMs tracked: ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity</div></div>
