  <!-- FEATURES IN DEPTH -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Features in depth</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Every major <span class="accent">Nightwatch feature</span>, tested.</h2>
      <p>What's in the platform — and how each piece holds up against the competition.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Visual rank tracking</h4>
              <p>Daily ranking updates, 107,000+ locations with ZIP-code precision, multi-engine tracking (Google, Bing, Yahoo, DuckDuckGo, YouTube, Maps), SERP feature detection, mobile vs. desktop split, and 3-year historical SERP archives. This is the core product — and it's excellent. The dashboards are clean, the data is accurate (96–98% in our testing), and competitor tracking covers 5–15 competitors per site.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>AI and LLM tracking (2026)</h4>
              <p>Citation Intelligence monitors brand and keyword mentions across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity. Shows AI citation correlation alongside traditional SERP rankings. Also includes SEO MCP integration with Claude, Cursor, and ChatGPT — useful for teams building AI-assisted workflows. This feature alone separates Nightwatch from most rank trackers in 2026.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Site audit</h4>
              <p>100+ technical checks: 404 errors, redirects, metadata issues, duplicates, speed. JavaScript rendering support, broken link detection, 0–100 site health scoring, historical comparison. Solid as a secondary feature. The 25-page limit on Starter is a real problem for production sites — if you're relying on this for deep technical audits, budget for Agency or use Screaming Frog alongside.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>White-label reporting</h4>
              <p>Fully customizable client dashboards, automated daily/weekly/monthly scheduling, branded PDF and HTML exports, Looker Studio integration on Professional+ plans, and unlimited user seats across all tiers. The strongest reporting layer of any rank tracker we tested — agencies will get genuine value here.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>NightOwl SEO agent (2026)</h4>
              <p>Monitors competitor ranking changes, identifies content opportunities, suggests meta optimizations, and can execute tasks via MCP. Early-stage but directionally interesting. Worth watching rather than relying on for production workflows yet.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">06</span>
            <div>
              <h4>What's missing</h4>
              <p>Content writing, auto-publishing, Google Business Profile management, local citation building, social media distribution, and deep backlink analysis. Nightwatch is a tracking and reporting tool. Building the rankings it tracks requires a separate content and local SEO workflow.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PRICING -->
  <section class="cost-section">
    <div class="cost-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Pricing</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">What Nightwatch <span class="accent">actually costs.</span></h2>
      <p>Four tiers, all with unlimited seats and white-label reporting. Annual billing saves 20%.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cost-table">
      <div class="cost-row head">
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Plan</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Monthly</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Annual</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell brand">Key limits</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Starter</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Solo / small teams</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">€79</div><div class="per">per month</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">€63</div><div class="per">per month</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;">500 keywords · 5 sites · 25 audit pages</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Professional</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Growing agencies</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">€159</div><div class="per">per month</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">€127</div><div class="per">per month</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;">2,500 keywords · 25 sites · Looker Studio · API</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Agency</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Full-service agencies</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">€399</div><div class="per">per month</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">€319</div><div class="per">per month</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;">7,500 keywords · 100 sites · unlimited audits</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Enterprise</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Custom</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">Custom</div><div class="per"></div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">Custom</div><div class="per"></div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;">20,000+ keywords · unlimited · SSO · custom integrations</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-savings">
        <div class="big">Tracking + content = the full stack.</div>
        <div class="lbl">Nightwatch tracks the rankings. theStacc builds them — 30 articles/month, GBP automation, and social distribution for $49/mo.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-footnote">*All plans include unlimited team seats, white-label reporting, 107,000+ tracking locations, 3-year SERP history, 14-day free trial, and SOC 2 compliance. Prices in EUR.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Who it's for</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Who should buy Nightwatch — <span class="accent">and who shouldn't.</span></h2>
      <p>The clearest filter we found after testing across local SEO, reporting, and AI tracking use cases.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Buy Nightwatch if</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">You're a local SEO agency.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Three signals Nightwatch fits.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>You need ZIP-code level local tracking</h4><p>No competitor matches Nightwatch's local granularity. If your clients are service-area businesses or multi-location retail, this is the tool.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>You need white-label client reporting at scale</h4><p>Unlimited seats, branded dashboards, automated scheduling — all on every plan. Agencies with 10+ clients will save hours per month on reporting.</p></div></li>
